<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862i.01/144½</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Embassy</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi><note n="35" xml:id="d280fn35">Handed to the Secretary of State by the Japanese
                                Ambassador, June 18.</note></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" type="received-date" when="1921-06-18">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="flushleft">(Tentative draft)</p>
                        <p>It is agreed that the United States shall have free access to the Island
                            of Yap on the footing of entire equality with Japan or any other nation,
                            in all that relates to the landing and operation of the existing
                            Yap–Guam cable or of any cable which may hereafter be laid by the United
                            States or its nationals.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>